# Code Review Rules

> Separate from CLAUDE.md build rules. These are review-specific instructions.
> Based on the Anthropic Code Review pattern (March 2026): review rules belong in their own file.

## Review Scope
When reviewing code, check ONLY the following. Do not flag style preferences or suggest refactors outside this list.

## Rules

### Security (P0 — always block)
- [ ] No secrets, API keys, or tokens in source code
- [ ] RLS policies on every Supabase table
- [ ] Auth middleware on all protected routes
- [ ] Zod validation on every server action input
- [ ] No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without sanitization
- [ ] No raw SQL — use parameterized Supabase client
- [ ] File uploads validated (size, type, filename)

### Correctness (P0 — always block)
- [ ] Server actions handle errors with try/catch
- [ ] Form validation shows user-friendly messages
- [ ] Data mutations revalidate the correct paths
- [ ] Auth signOut uses `{ scope: 'local' }`
- [ ] No `use client` on page-level components

### Performance (P1 — should fix)
- [ ] No N+1 queries (batch fetches where possible)
- [ ] Images optimized (WebP, max 1200px, lazy loading)
- [ ] No unnecessary client components (default to server)
- [ ] No blocking waterfall fetches (parallel where possible)

### Mobile (P1 — should fix)
- [ ] Touch targets ≥ 48px on all interactive elements
- [ ] Responsive breakpoints on layout components
- [ ] Bottom navigation on mobile (if applicable)
- [ ] Forms usable on 393px viewport
- [ ] No horizontal scroll on mobile

### Patterns (P2 — nice to fix)
- [ ] Follows CLAUDE.md file structure conventions
- [ ] Server actions for mutations, not API routes
- [ ] Consistent error handling pattern
- [ ] Loading states on async pages (loading.tsx)
- [ ] Empty states on data display pages

## Priority Definitions
- **P0:** Must fix before merge. Blocks deployment.
- **P1:** Should fix before delivery. Can merge with a follow-up ticket.
- **P2:** Nice to fix. Won't block anything.

## Review Output Format
```
## Review: [file or feature name]

### P0 Issues (X found)
- [file:line] — [issue] → [fix]

### P1 Issues (X found)
- [file:line] — [issue] → [fix]

### P2 Issues (X found)
- [file:line] — [issue] → [fix]

### Verdict: APPROVE / REQUEST CHANGES / BLOCK
```
